I use an arduino uno-r3 (Which is using atmega328p) to learn avr instructions.
To upload assembly program to Arduino. Run the following commands:

$ avr-as -g -mmcu=atmega328p -o your_program.o your_program.s
$ avr-ld -o your_program.elf your_program.o
$ avr-objcopy -O ihex -R .eeprom your_program.elf your_program.hex
$ avrdude -C /etc/avrdude.conf -p atmega328p -c arduino -P /dev/ttyACM0 \
-b 115200 -D -U flash:w:your_program.hex:i

For more details, you can check out the link below.

    https://www.cypherpunk.at/2014/09/native-assembler-programming-on-arduino/
